European countries have now been involved in the Pacific region for thirty years, and are major donors to the area.
It is therefore particularly important to develop a long-term strategy.
This is actually the only part of the world for which the Union has not yet developed a overarching, integrated strategy.
The adoption of the document under consideration represents an excellent opportunity to create a new relationship with this region.
This relationship should be both economic and political.
