Can he promise that the Committee on International Trade, which has just elected its new chairman this morning, will also be kept informed?
on behalf of the UEN Group. - (PL) Madam President, it is entirely appropriate for the House to be dealing with the question of the greater liberalisation of public procurement markets today, and I believe it is regrettable that the same determination was lacking when we debated the liberalisation of services across our continent.
Essentially, the issues are the same.
